New Records: Aged 34 years and 131 days, Baumann is the second oldest player to make his Germany debut in the post-war era.
Key Match Events: Jamie Leweling scored the winning goal for Germany in the 64th minute.
Oliver Baumann made a brilliant save to tip Xavi's thunderous strike onto the crossbar.
Baumann made another crucial save in added time to thwart Donyell Malen.
Pre-Game Insights: German football paid tribute to recently retired international quartet Manuel Neuer, Thomas Müller, Toni Kroos, and İlkay Gündogan prior to kick-off.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany secured their place in the 2024/25 UEFA Nations League knockouts with victory over the Netherlands.
Germany remains unbeaten and top of Group A3, progressing to the Nations League quarter-final stage with two group games to spare.
